.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-DOWN" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.33" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-down \- Cancel a tracked job and clean tracked state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose down [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Cancel a tracked Slurm job by compose context or job id, remove tracked metadata and runtime state for that job, and optionally purge its tracked cached image artifacts.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to cancel instead of the latest recorded submission.
.TP
\fB--scancel\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the scancel executable. Default: scancel.
.TP
\fB--purge\-cache\fR
Also purge tracked cached image artifacts for this job.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose down \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose down \-\-job\-id 12345
hpc\-compose down \-\-job\-id 12345 \-\-purge\-cache
.fi
